In line with the population rating scores, priming emotional images (negative, neutral and positive) differed both in valence (X 2 (2)=403.19; p<0.001) and
arousal (X 2 (2)=156.11; p<0.001) ratings in our sample. Likewise, foods and objects differed in valence (X 2 (1)=8.91; p<0.003) and arousal (X 2 (1)=41.80;
p<0.001) ratings, with food stimuli obtaining higher scores for both measures (Figure 2) .
